OL,3,CHusband and parents jailed for abusing
OL,4,Cand burning arranged marriage bride
OL,6,F"You would all have been aware of her
OL,7,Fpain and distress," said Judge
OL,8,FLambert. "It's just not realistic to
OL,9,Fconclude that you did not all know of
OL,10,FAmbreen's predicament and her
OL,11,Fdesperate need for emergency medical
OL,12,Fcare.
OL,14,F"You all also knew why she was in that
OL,15,Fcondition."
OL,17,FThe court heard that Ms Sheikh is now
OL,18,Fbeing looked after in a palliative
OL,19,Fcare setting and will not recover, but
OL,20,Fcould live for decades more.
